<h1>COMB - Number of combinations</h1>

[[COMB(N,M)]] returns the number of combinations of [[N]] things,
taken [[M]] at a time.

<h2>Uses</h2>
<a href=".html"></a><br>

<<INCLUDES>>=
@

<<COMB>>=
-MODULE COMB
-PUBLIC COMB()
         DEFINE('COMB(N,M)')                                 :(COMB_END)
*
COMB     COMB = EQ(M, 0) 1                                    :S(RETURN)
         COMB = COMB(N - 1, M - 1) * N / M                     :(RETURN)
*
COMB_END
@

<<unit_test>>=
#!/usr/bin/bash
         exec "snobol4" "-b" "$0" "$@"
-INCLUDE 'COMB.INC'
         &CODE = 1
         &CODE = 0
END
@

